Synopsis:
Yash Raj Films’ Saiyaara is an intense love story, that launches Ahaan Panday and Aneet Padda as the next YRF hero and heroine respectively. 

Directed by Mohit Suri, a master of the romance genre, Saiyaara tells a pure-hearted love story of two youngsters Vaani and Krish. While Vaani writes, Krish sings and they both make music together. Though poles apart in their lives, beliefs and backgrounds, Vaani and Krish are perfect with each other and for each other. Will they understand that truth despite their age, their problems? 

They say flawed, imperfect people make for a perfect love story…and Saiyaara is about celebrating that one love story that is so deep, so pure and so caring that it is absolutely unconditional.

Vaani and Krish will have to navigate life, their problems, their insecurities to hopefully realise that only love can be the answer to everything. Saiyaara is a film that celebrates every season of love through the eyes of Vaani & Krish and poses a simple question…do you love someone so much that you would bet everything to keep that person in your life?

snippet.title: Piya Ghar Aaya - Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan (Asad's Remix)
snippet.description:
All praise to Ustaad Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan.

I'm excited to finally share the full version. Thanks for waiting so patiently (most of you :p)
I'm starting off my new series called EIGHT x EIGHT with this track, As a part of this series I'll put out a new song every Thursday for the next 8 weeks

I grew up in Pakistan, and I now live in Canada. My family is from Faisalabad. Growing up, my grandfather listened to a lot of qawwali around me as a kid and that influence never left my dna. After years of making music, I finally did something with a track from Ustaad Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan. I also really enjoyed seeing videos of this track from all over the world, specially from home - thank you for sharing those. 

This remix blew up on TikTok, Instagram etc but more importantly, as you can see in this video, it created a beautiful moment for a group of people and that's what music is all about. Ustaad Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan's legacy continues to serve moments like this, I'm grateful to have been a vessel. 

Thanks for showing this so much love, lots more music soon

Asad

LYRICS:
Ali hi haq tha Ali hi haq hai Ali ki naslon mein haq rahe ga
Ali viraasat hai Mustafa ki, Ali hi mash’hood-e-haq rahe ga

Tu wo walad hai jo lam-yalid ke makaan se jalwa-numa hua hai
Tu nashir-e-dawa-e-salooni, tu kya hai? Sab ko guman hua hai
Tu qasim-e-noor-e-Mustafa hai, tu nafs-e-Payghambar-e-Khuda hai
Tu markaz-e-Awliya-e-alam, tu bil-yaqeen fakhr-e-Ambiya hai

Ali mizaaj-e-Muhammadi hai, Ali to asrar-e-haq rahe ga
Ali hi haq tha Ali hi haq hai Ali ki naslon mein haq rahe ga

Tu hi Risaalat ki hai khilafat, tu hi wilayat tu hi imamat
Tu kurra-e-arz-e-Kibriya pe Nabi ki hai awaleen shahadat
Tu mehvar-e-ilm-e-do-sara hai, tu kashif-e-maqsad-e-ibadat
Tu hai siraat-e-nijaat-e-insaan, hai qalb-e-momin teri riyasat

Tumhara rahbar tumhain mubarak, hamara rahbar Ali rahe ga
Ali hi haq tha Ali hi haq hai Ali ki naslon mein haq rahe ga

Wo badr ho ya mubahila ho, ya phir Muhammad ki wo kisaa ho
Wo chahe Marhab ka samna ho, ya phir wo khandaq ka ma’rka ho
Uhud mein dhaal-e-Payambari ya, buton ka Ka’be se khaatma ho
Ya wo wilayat ki taaj-poshi ba-dast-e-at'haar-e-Mustafa ho

Ali se daman bachane wale, Ali tujhe jaa ba jaa mile ga
Ali hi haq tha Ali hi haq hai Ali ki naslon mein haq rahe ga

Nabi ke deen ki ragon mein Haider lahu ki soorat ravaan rahe ga
Ali ka munkir zaleel-o-ruswa azal se tha hashr tak rahe ga
Ali hi haq tha Ali hi haq hai Ali ki naslon mein haq rahe ga

Bus Ali Ali Bus Ali Ali ...

Aao ji Ali Ali wird paka laiyay
Ghaman nu chadd aj khushiyan mana laiyay
Ral ke aakhiye, “Baad Muhammad
Sab ton afzal zikr-e-Ali" Bus

Ali Ali Bus Ali Ali Bus ...

Ali de chehre nu takna ibadat
Ali da naan loko japna ibadat
Ki ki mein dassan tenu sifat Ali di
Jane Ali nu Khuda Ya Nabi bus

Ali Ali Bus Ali Ali Bus ...

Haider, safdar, sher-e-ghazanfar
Rahbar-e-akbar, mard-e-muzaffar
At'har, azhar, Haq da mazhar
Peeng de andar cheereya azdar
Deen da anbar, Khvaja Qambar
Veer Paighambar, awwal number
Baad Muhammad sab ton bartar
Ikko baan nal puteya Khyber
Ilm samandar, fakhr-e-Sikandar
Mard-e-Qalandar, loon loon andar
Badr ton lay ke Khandak, Khyber
Dushman cheer ke langeya Haider
Tayyab, tahir, banda-parwar
Rooh-e-munawwar, maula, sarwar
Hadi, mahdi, aali-gauhar
Zahra paak da suchha shauhar
Qazi-e-azam, alim-e-alam
Shams-e-wilayat, Noor-e-hidayat
Aashiq Rab da, Paak nasab da
Ghaiz ghazab da, Hunar kasab da
Mahir sab da, Fakhr Arab da
Baap Hassan da, Phol chaman da
Raah adan da, shah zaman da 
Waar Ali da, kair Khuda da
Ishq Ali da, lutf Khuda da
Bol Ali de, hukam Khuda da
Deed Ali di, karam Khuda da

Bus Ali Ali Bus Ali Ali Bus ...

snippet.title: Tron: Ares | Official Trailer
snippet.description:
Watch the brand-new trailer for Tron: Ares and experience it in theaters, filmed for IMAX, October 10.
 
Tron: Ares follows a highly sophisticated Program, Ares, who is sent from the digital world into the real world on a dangerous mission, marking humankind’s first encounter with A.I. beings. The feature film is directed by Joachim Rønning and stars Jared Leto, Greta Lee, Evan Peters, Hasan Minhaj, Jodie Turner-Smith, Arturo Castro, Cameron Monaghan, with Gillian Anderson, and Jeff Bridges. Sean Bailey, Jeffrey Silver, Justin Springer, Jared Leto, Emma Ludbrook and Steven Lisberger are the producers, with Russell Allen serving as executive producer.

Grammy®-award winning rock band Nine Inch Nails composed the score for “Tron: Ares,” and today, the band dropped "As Alive As You Need Me To Be" —the soundtrack album’s first single and the first official music from the band in five years. Listen to "As Alive As You Need Me To Be” and view the visualizer: https://nineinchnails.lnk.to/AAAYNMTB. The track is featured in the new trailer for “Tron: Ares.”
 
“Tron: Ares (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack),” featuring all original music by Nine Inch Nails, will be released on September 19 via Interscope Records. The release marks the first-ever film score by the pioneering band, although bandmates Trent Reznor and Atticus Ross have composed 20 scores under their own names, winning two Oscars®, three Golden Globes®, a GRAMMY® and an Emmy® in the process.
